"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627323","Department for Education","false","2016-11-07","<p>Higher education institutions (HEIs) in England are independent and autonomous bodies. They are responsible for the management of their own internal affairs, including the provision and administration of student residential accommodation.</p><p> </p><p>This Department plays no direct role in the provision of student residential accommodation whether the accommodation is managed by universities or private sector organisations.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-11-07T17:53:34.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627323/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627323/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627323/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-02","Students: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will take steps to limit increases in the cost of student accommodation.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","51531"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627324","Department for Education","false","2016-11-08","<p>Since the free schools programme began, 98 free school projects have had their opening date deferred. In each case there was a need to balance the risk of opening on the planned date against all the elements that must be in place to ensure that a free school is successful when it opens. Our guidance makes clear that allowing a free school project to enter the “pre-opening” phase does not guarantee that the school will open on the date originally planned by the proposer group, or open at all.</p><p>Free schools offer excellent value for money. The National Audit Office found in 2013 that free schools were built 45% more cheaply than other school building programmes. The free schools that are already open will provide over 180,000 new places.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-11-08T18:12:54.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627324/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627324/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627324/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-02","Free Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many free schools were delayed in opening in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","51533"
