oreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-02","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what proportion of women are employed by his Department on an inner London pay structure in the following pay grades (a) Administrative Assistant, (b) Administrative Officer, (c) Executive Officer, (d) Higher Executive Officer, (e) Fast Streamer, (f) Senior Executive Officer, (g) Grade Seven, (h) Grade Six, (i) Senior Civil Service Band 1, (j) Senior Civil Service Band 1A, (k) Senior Civil Service Band 2 and (l) Senior Civil Service Band 3.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","51555"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627354","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-08","<p>While we have not made any assessment on this specific issue, we regularly urge the Palestinian and Israeli leaderships to refrain from or prevent any actions that could threaten the viability of a two-state solution, including violence, incitement and settlement expansion. We continue to support the reinstatement of the Tripartite Committee on Incitement as the appropriate channel to deal with allegations of incitement from either side, and continue to press the Palestinian Authority (PA) regularly on the importance of their swift condemnation of violent attacks.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-08T14:57:47.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627354/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627354/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627354/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-02","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the implications of the ongoing glorification sanctioned by the Palestinian Authority of people who have killed Israelis for the viability of a lasting two-state solution.","false","Biography information for Bob Blackman","Harrow East","Bob Blackman","51552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627355","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-08","<p>Access to essential medical treatment is an important issue, and our officials at the British Embassy in Tel Aviv will seek appropriate opportunities to raise this.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-08T14:59:44.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627355/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627355/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627355/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-02","Palestinians: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 28 October 2016 to Question 50165, if he will raise with the Israeli government the issue of access to essential medical treatment for people living in Palestinian territories.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","51606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627357","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-08","<p>The British Government continues to call on the Honduran Government to uphold all human rights, including the right to peaceful protest. I raised the importance of human rights with the President of Honduras' Congress during his visit to London in September. Our Ambassador to Honduras (based in Guatemala City) also discusses human rights issues with the Honduran authorities during her frequent visits to the country.</p><p>We encourage all governments to create a safe and enabling environment for all civil society. Whilst we recognise that some progress has been made by the Honduran Government, recent high profile cases, including that of Berta Cáceres, have shown that more still needs to be done.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2016-11-08T16:08:15.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627357/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627357/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627357/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-02","Honduras: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the government of Honduras on human rights activists and the right to peaceful protest in that country.","false","Biography information for Ann Clwyd","Cynon Valley","Ann Clwyd","51593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627358","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-10","<p>There have been no such discussions.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2016-11-10T16:43:03.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627358/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627358/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627358/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-02","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Mossack Fonseca","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has had any discussions with representatives of the firm Mossack Fonseca since April 2016.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart Malcolm McDonald","51590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627360","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-07","<p>​​I refer the Rt Hon. Member to my answers of 24 October 2016 (PQ 49493) and 27 October 2016 (PQ 49939).</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-07T11:49:59.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627360/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627360/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627360/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-02","Middle East: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how much funding the Government is providing to each (a) Israeli and (b) Palestinian non-governmental organisation through the (i) Conflict, Security and Stability Fund and (ii) bilateral programme budget in 2016-17.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","51536"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627361","Department of Health","false","2016-11-07","<p>No assessment has been made as we do not collect data on the extent of sleep-overs, so are not in a position to estimate costs.</p><p> </p><p>Under the Care Act 2014, local authorities must have regard to fostering an effective workforce with the appropriate capabilities when shaping their local markets. The Act and its statutory guidance make clear that prices and fee rates agreed with providers must reflect these duties.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-11-07T12:13:48.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627361/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627361/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627361/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-11-02","Social Services: Living Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether his Department has made an assessment of the potential level of cost pressures on learning disability service provider wage budgets arising from the application of the national living wage to sleep-in shifts.","false","Biography information for Peter Aldous","Waveney","Peter Aldous","51566"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627364","Department of Health","false","2016-11-08","<p>NHS Digital publishes workforce statistics and the following table shows the age profile of midwives working in the National Health Service in England at 30 September 2005, 2010 and 2015. Data for July 2016 is also provided as this is the latest available.</p><p> </p><p>The data is headcount because equality data relates to individuals.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-11-08T11:33:41.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627364/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627364/answer","PQ51597 midwives table.xlsx","PQ51597 midwives table.xlsx","PQ51597 midwives table","PQ51597 midwives table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627364/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-11-02","Midwives: Age","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the age profile of midwives working in the NHS in England was in (a) the most recent year for which figures are available, (b) 2010 and (c) 2005.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","51597"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627365","Department of Health","false","2016-11-08","<p>The aims of the community pharmacy reforms are to improve the service offered to the public, make better use of pharmacists’ valuable clinical skills, and allocate taxpayers’ money more efficiently. Those reforms do not have a proposal on a smaller number of large volume pharmacies reducing costs or improving NHS services.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-11-08T14:46:16.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627365/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627365/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627365/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-11-02","Pharmacy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the evidential basis is for his Department's proposal on a smaller number of large volume pharmacies reducing costs or improving NHS services.","false","Biography information for Sir David Crausby","Bolton North East","Mr David Crausby","51603"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627366","Department of Health","false","2016-11-08","<p>One of the aims of the community pharmacy reforms is to encourage much greater use of community pharmacy as a first port of call by fully integrating it with the rest of the National Health Service, so that more people benefit from the skills of pharmacists and their teams – including in general practitioner (GP) practices, urgent care hubs and out of hours services. It will also relieve pressure on other parts of the NHS, by embedding community pharmacy into the urgent care pathway.</p><p>The new Pharmacy Integration Fund will drive the greater use of community pharmacy, pharmacists and pharmacy technicians in new, integrated local care models. This will improve access for patients, relieve the pressure on GPs and accident and emergency departments, ensure optimal use of medicines, drive better value, improve patient outcomes, and contribute to delivering a seven day health and care service.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-11-08T16:20:11.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627366/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627366/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627366/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-11-02","Pharmacy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the potential savings which community pharmacies can make to clinical commissioning group budgets.","false","Biography information for Sir David Crausby","Bolton North East","Mr David Crausby","51604"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627367","Department of Health","false","2016-11-08","<p>Ministers have regular meetings with NHS Improvement and the Care Quality Commission to discuss a variety of issues.</p><p> </p><p>The redesign and delivery of front-line health services is a matter for the local National Health Service – clinically led by front-line NHS organisations and clinicians who are closest to the needs of communities and therefore best-placed to make decisions in the interests of their patients.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-11-08T09:08:20.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627367/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627367/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627367/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-11-02","Accident and Emergency Departments: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, which Ministers of his Department have met with NHS Improvement and the Care Quality Commission in which weeks since 11 July 2016; and at which of those meetings specific accident and emergency department closures were discussed.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","51550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627368","Department of Health","false","2016-11-08","<p>The information requested for civil servants employed by the Department as at 30 September 2016 is given in the table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Grade</p></td><td><p>Number of females in grade</p></td><td><p>Percentage of females in grade on Inner London Pay Scale</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>AO</p></td><td><p>53</p></td><td><p>64%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>EO</p></td><td><p>231</p></td><td><p>71%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HEO</p></td><td><p>174</p></td><td><p>62%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>SEO</p></td><td><p>183</p></td><td><p>50%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>FAST ST</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p>Not applicable *</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>GRADE 7</p></td><td><p>275</p></td><td><p>64%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>GRADE 6</p></td><td><p>109</p></td><td><p>74%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>SCS 1</p></td><td><p>48</p></td><td><p>Not applicable *</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>SCS 2</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>Not applicable *</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>SCS 3</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>Not applicable *</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>1,111</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>* - There are no separate inner London pay scales for SCS and Fast Stream staff</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-11-08T14:44:24.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627368/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627368/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627368/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-11-02","Department of Health: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what proportion of women are employed by his Department on an inner London pay structure in the following pay grades (a) Administrative Assistant, (b) Administrative Officer, (c) Executive Officer, (d) Higher Executive Officer, (e) Fast Streamer, (f) Senior Executive Officer, (g) Grade Seven, (h) Grade Six, (i) Senior Civil Service Band 1, (j) Senior Civil Service Band 1A, (k) Senior Civil Service Band 2 and (l) Senior Civil Service Band 3.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","51556"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627369","Department of Health","false","2016-11-08","<p>The Government believes efficiencies can be made within community pharmacy without compromising the quality of services or public access to them. Following recent growth in the number of community pharmacies, 40% of pharmacies are now in clusters of three or more. In fact, two-fifths of pharmacies are within 10 minutes’ walk of at least two other pharmacies. As part of the community pharmacy reforms, we are introducing a Pharmacy Access Scheme to support access where pharmacies are sparsely spread and patients depend on them most. We will have a review process to deal with any unforeseen circumstances affecting access; like a road closure. We will also review cases where there may be a high level of deprivation and pharmacies are 0.8 of a mile or more from another pharmacy, if that pharmacy is critical for access.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-11-08T14:45:15.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627369/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627369/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627369/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-11-02","Pharmacy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to the letter of 17 December 2015 from the Director General, Innovation, Growth and Technology, and the Chief Pharmaceutical Officer supporting NHS England, to the Chief Executive of the Pharmaceutical Services Negotiating Committee, in which parts of the country there are more pharmacies than are necessary to maintain good access.","false","Biography information for Sir David Crausby","Bolton North East","Mr David Crausby","51662"
