"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627432","Leader of the House","false","2016-11-07","<p>Government has not made a cost estimate for the implementation of English Votes for English Laws because it constitutes parliamentary business.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-11-07T14:23:37.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627432/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627432/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/627432/answer",,,,,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2016-11-02","English Votes for English Laws","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, what estimate he has made of the cost of implementation of the English Votes for English Laws Standing Orders of the House of Commons; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","51699"
